1970-01-01 00:12:00 To make the base:

Mix together your bread flour, yeast and salt in a large mixing bowl.

Make a small hole in the centre of the mix and add water slowly, mixing as you go until the dough starts to form.

Once you have a ball of dough, take this out of the bowl, put flour in the surface so it does not stick and kneed the dough. 

Once kneeded then roll it into a flat circle ready for topping. Leave it for 15 minutes or more to prove.

Preheat your oven to 200 °C or gas mark 5

Add the pasta to the provide based, spreading evenly across the base without reaching the edges.

Add toppings, cheese to your preference, and seasoning.

Cook for 12 minutes, take out, slice and enjoy.
